Gulf Stocks: Qatar’s Aamal and Oman’s Raysut Cement Advance

-- B y   Z a h r a   H a n k i r
-- 
2011-05-22T14:38:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-22/gulf-stocks-oman-s-raysut-cement-saudi-s-sahara-petrochemical.html
The  DFM General Index (DFMGI)  retreated for a
second day, dropping 0.3 percent to 1,578.68 at the 2 p.m. close
in Dubai. Qatar’s  QE Index (DSM)  declined 0.4 percent.  The following stocks rose or fell in the Persian Gulf
region. Symbols are in parentheses.        Raysut Cement Co. (RCCI)   climbed the most in a week,
gaining 1.2 percent to 1.064 rials. Oman’s biggest cement-maker
by market value was raised to “neutral” from “sell” at EFG-
Hermes Holding SAE.        Aamal Co. (AHCS)   had its biggest two-day surge on
record, soaring 21 percent, the most since December 2007, to
22.14 riyals. The stock rallied 10 percent today. The Qatari
holding company will list shares in the form of global
depositary receipts on the London Stock Exchange next month to
“enhance the profile” of the company, Chief Operating Officer
Mohamed Dobashi said May 18.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Zahra Hankir in Dubai at 
 zhankir@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
